    "Table 1 is an example of how the Large Language Model GPT -3.5 could be used to simulate a synthetic user which shares many crucial characteristics with the original.",
    "Having the artificially intelligent pollster learn from massive amounts of synthetic data preserves its ability to generate accurate predictions while obviating privacy concerns in the data collection and storage phase altogether.",
    "Under a differential privacy framework, the privacy risk from mass collection and storage of data is minimised.",
    "In addition, the need to store information about any 'real person' is dwindling thanks to advances in generative deep learning.",
    "Note that these practices have already been adopted by most major tech companies, with Apple leading the path."
